SIMPLE: civic
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Civic
<hw>Civ"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.civicus, fr.
<ets>civis</ets> citizen. See <er>City</er>.]</ety> <def>Relating to, or
derived from, a city or citizen; relating to man as a member of society,
or to civil affairs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Civic crown</b></col> <fld>(Rom. Antiq.)</fld>, <cd>a
crown or garland of oak leaves and acorns, bestowed on a soldier who had
saved the life of a citizen in battle.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Civicism</ent>⟦br⟧
